566				// route-health TTL window. Historical tracker timestamps (minutes
567				// to ~15 min old) sit outside fizeau's default 30s cooldown and
568				// are dropped immediately by ActiveAttempts, leaving policy/default
569				// Execute routes free to re-pick the same failed provider. The
570				// tracker-side cutoff above (ProviderUnavailableCooldown) decides
571				// which failures are still worth replaying; once they pass that
572				// gate they are asserted active for fizeau's TTL counted from now.
573				_ = svc.RecordRouteAttempt(ctx, agentlib.RouteAttempt{
574					Provider:  failed.Provider,
